  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance to Conflict Affected Individuals in the Central African Republic (CAR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Central African Republic (CAR) has been plunged into a complex political and security crisis that has involved various actors since 2013 and has led to a protracted humanitarian situation of concern. The most recent crisis emerged at the end of 2020 and beginning of 2021. IOM&#x2019;s emergency response has the general objective to contribute to improving the living conditions of conflict affected populations through data collection, information sharing, and shelter/non-food item (NFI) support. The project proposes the implementation of various components of the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) to inform the humanitarian community and government counterparts of the most pressing, multisectoral needs in places hosting the highest concentration of internally displaced persons and returnees. The DTM activities are accompanied by the immediate provision of emergency shelter, NFIs and COVID-19 prevention kits to the displaced populations affected by the recent humanitarian shocks.</narrative>
  </description>
